# Password-protects the /team page (or whatever path you put the app at) using Netlify's
# Basic Auth support. Works on every Netlify plan, no upgrade needed.
#
# To change the password: edit the line below, commit, push — Netlify picks it up on the
# next deploy (usually live within a minute or two).
#
# To give different staff their own login instead of one shared password, add more
# Basic-Auth lines under the same path, one per person, e.g.:
#   Basic-Auth: shantelle:herpassword
#   Basic-Auth: dijana:herpassword
# Each line is a separate valid login — handy if someone leaves and you only want to
# revoke their line rather than changing everyone's password.

/team/*
  Basic-Auth: team:2332
